"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-coco-gauff-2024-olympics-elimination-mixed-doubles\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Coco Gauff's first Olympic experience has come to an end following losses in the women's singles, the women's doubles and the mixed doubles tournaments.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 20 years old, Gauff was chasing an Olympic medal, but unfortunately could not get it done.\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She lost in dramatic fashion in the singles draw on Tuesday to Croatia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Donna Vekic in the third round.Gauff was brought to tearswhen arguing with the umpire about a call in the final set.\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gauff and her women's doubles partner Jessica Pegula lost on Wednesday in the second round to the Czech duo of Linda Noskov\\u00c3\\u00a1 and Karol\\u00c3\\u00adna Muchov\\u00c3\\u00a1 in a tiebreak.\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Pegula\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\"}, {\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999614997169906, \"rank\": 2.7039597094576683e-05, \"text\": \"Czech\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"